1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:07,963
Now pay attention here,  this next idea changes everything,  Manual sync commit (commitSync()): Blocks until the broker confirms the commit.

2
00:00:07,913 --> 00:00:12,096
Guarantees at-least-once — if processing succeeds, commit succeeds.

3
00:00:12,096 --> 00:00:16,855
If the consumer crashes before committing, messages are reprocessed on restart.

4
00:00:16,855 --> 00:00:22,519
Fun fact: Uber processes ride data in real-time — handling one billion events per day.

5
00:00:22,519 --> 00:00:24,153
Let that sink in.

